Body:
I am studying IOT-server. I have a question and please help me. I use WSO2 IoT server and I am not able to access WSO2 IoT server device Management Console (https://localhost:9443/devicemgt) when I input 'admin' both username and password or input this which created a new account.
As a result
column9: it showed me the Authentication failed. When I saw users list in https://localhost:9443/carbon
column11:
new accounts .... etc. I don't know why it does not log in WSO2 IoT server device Management Console. Please give your advice and then thank you so much.

"

Body: You need to check Java version, All wso2 Products have issues with the latest version of Java, if you are using java version 1.8.0_151" then that's a problem
column9:
try using java version "1.8.0_144". If you cannot change java version then you need to change the compression parameter to off in catalina-server.xml file

"

Body: Thank you so much. I tried that. I saw java version 1.8.0_181" and compression ="off" . I modified that. Perfectly it does well. Thank you so much again."
Welcome, can you accept the answer so that it will be helpful for others as well.
